[h1]Phobos' Industrial Pathways: Biomass[/h1]

[b]Version:[/b] 1.2.0 | [b]Requires:[/b] Project Zomboid Build 42.14.0+ | [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3668598865]PhobosLib 1.16.0+[/url] | [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3615135168]Zombie Virus Vaccine[/url]

A complete industrial chemistry and biomass processing suite for Project Zomboid Build 42, adding realistic crafting pathways for blackpowder, biodiesel, soap, bone char, salt extraction, agriculture, recycling, botanical hemp processing, horticulture, and advanced laboratory processes.

[i]Part of the Phobos' Industrial Pathways mod series.[/i]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Features[/h2]

[h3]Applied Chemistry Skill System[/h3]
Custom Applied Chemistry perk with a steeper XP curve (75-9000). Two occupations (Chemist and Pharmacist) and two traits (Chemistry Enthusiast and Chemical Aversion) provide starting skill bonuses. Five skill book volumes cover levels 1-10. All 276 recipes award Applied Chemistry XP with 7 tiers of skill requirements.

[h3]Blackpowder Pathway[/h3]
Seven-step chain from raw charcoal to gunpowder: crush, purify (water or alkaline wash), prepare compost, extract battery acid, extract sulphur, synthesize potassium nitrate, and mix blackpowder.

[h3]Biodiesel Pathway[/h3]
Five-step chain from raw crops to refined vehicle fuel. Extract oil from 6 crop types (soybeans, sunflower, corn, flax, hemp, peanuts) using 3 equipment tiers (mortar and pestle, chemistry set, metal drum). Transesterify with methanol and KOH or NaOH catalyst, water-wash, and refine into usable fuel.

[h3]Fat Rendering & Oil Conversion[/h3]
Render lard, butter, or margarine into biodiesel feedstock. Slow-cook butchered meat cuts (6 pieces to 2 jars of rendered fat + bone scraps) in a cooking pot — a renewable fat source from animal husbandry. Convert bottled vegetable or olive oil directly.

[h3]Soap-Making[/h3]
Two soap pathways: glycerol-based crude soap from biodiesel by-products, and traditional fat-based soap from rendered animal fats. Both support KOH and NaOH catalysts.

[h3]Bone Char Production[/h3]
Pyrolyse animal bones and skulls in metal drums to produce bone char, an alternative to purified charcoal in filtration and reagent recipes.

[h3]Salt Extraction Pathway[/h3]
Collect brine from water wells, concentrate through evaporation, crystallize into rock salt, and purify into table salt. Six-step chain using condition-based purity tracking. Right-click water wells to begin collection.

[h3]Recycling Pathway[/h3]
Nine-step recycling chain: wood tar to wood glue and tar-pitch torches, calcite to quicklime and fertilizer, crude soap to usable bars and sterilized bandages, lead scrap to fishing tackle, plastic scrap to glue, and acid-washed electronics to precision components.

[h3]Agriculture & Downstream Applications[/h3]
Six pathways connecting chemistry intermediates to vanilla gameplay systems:
[list]
[*] [b]Garden Pest Sprays[/b] — Sulphur fungicide (Mildew), insecticidal soap (Aphids), potash foliar (Flies) — functional B42 crop cures
[*] [b]Mineral Feed Supplements[/b] — Bone char-based animal feed
[*] [b]Water Purification[/b] — Activated charcoal filters and purification tablets; gas mask filter recharging
[*] [b]Epoxy Resin[/b] — Synthesized from wood tar and glycerol
[*] [b]Fire-Starting[/b] — Lighter fluid, matchboxes, slug repellent
[*] [b]Chemical Processing[/b] — Leather tanning, plaster powder, wood vinegar
[/list]

[h3]Botanical Pathway[/h3]
Thirty recipes for hemp processing: chemical retting with KOH or NaOH, fiber/hurd splitting, then branching into textiles (twine, rope, tarred rope, cloth, canvas), papermaking (pulp, chemical pulping, paper sheets), medicinals (poultice, tincture), and hurd processing (charcoal, hempcrete blocks, compost, fire bundles). Cross-links to blackpowder (charcoal from hurds), biodiesel (wood tar for tarring), and construction (hempcrete via concrete mixer). Gated by EnableBotanicalPathway sandbox option.

[h3]Horticulture Items[/h3]
31 items providing full parity with the [B42] Horticulture mod: tobacco (wet leaves, chewing tobacco in 3 container types), hemp buds (fresh, cured, decarboxylated, canned variants, ground loose), papermaking tools (mould and deckle, rolling papers), smoking products (glass pipe, loaded pipes, cigars, cigarettes, packs), and cooking (sugar syrup). Dual-trigger migration system converts existing Horticulture mod items to PCP equivalents.

[h3]Concrete Mixer Workstation[/h3]
Powered CraftBench entity for industrial-scale material processing. Build from a metal drum, salvaged motor, and welding equipment. Requires electricity (grid or generator). 13 recipes including concrete, mortar, reinforced concrete, and bulk chemistry operations. Generator fuel drain during crafting.

[h3]In-Game Guide & Changelog[/h3]
Welcome guide on first install with "Don't show again" option. Version-based "What's New" changelog popup on updates showing changes since your last played version.

[h3]Recipe Books[/h3]
Six lootable recipe books teaching PCP recipes by category, plus one master compendium:
[list]
[*] [b]Field Chemistry Primer[/b] — Blackpowder, recycling, and agriculture recipes
[*] [b]Kitchen Chemistry Companion[/b] — Fat rendering, soap, biodiesel, and cooking recipes
[*] [b]Laboratory Chemistry Reference[/b] — Advanced lab processes and salt extraction
[*] [b]Industrial Processes Manual[/b] — Concrete mixer and bulk processing recipes
[*] [b]Botanical Horticulture Guide[/b] — Hemp processing, textiles, and horticulture recipes
[*] [b]Complete Chemistry Compendium[/b] — Master volume teaching all PCP recipes
[/list]

[h3]Advanced Lab Equipment[/h3]
Centrifuge, chromatograph, microscope, and spectrometer recipes for enhanced processing. Microscope and spectrometer gated by sandbox option.

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Optional Systems[/h2]

[h3]Impurity/Purity System[/h3]
Condition-based purity tracking (0-100%) through recipe chains. Equipment quality factors, severity scaling, yield penalties, and player feedback via speech bubbles and custom tooltips.

[h3]Health Hazard System[/h3]
Hazard system for 11 dangerous chemistry recipes. Each splits into Protected (mask + goggles required, filter degrades) and Unprotected (risk of disease or stat penalties) variants. Integrates with EHR when available.

[h3]Empty Vessel Replacement[/h3]
Empty PCP FluidContainers automatically revert to their vanilla vessel equivalents (mason jar + lid, bottle, bucket, gas can) when you open a container. MP-synced.

[h3]Tiered Reset/Cleanup[/h3]
Six one-shot sandbox options for version upgrades, mod migration, and mod removal. Strip purity data, forget recipes, reset skill XP, remove all PCP items, migrate Horticulture items, or nuclear reset. Each executes once then auto-resets to OFF.

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Cross-Mod Integration[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]ZScienceSkill[/b] ("Science, Bitch!") — Applied Chemistry XP mirrors to Science at 50% rate; 52 items + 8 fluids registered as microscope specimens
[*] [b]EHR[/b] (Extensive Health Rework) — Health hazard recipes dispatch EHR diseases instead of vanilla stat penalties
[*] [b]Dynamic Trading[/b] — 59 PCP items registered for NPC trading with custom "Chemical" tag and "Chemist" trader archetype; chemical allocations injected into 8 existing vendor archetypes
[*] [b]Neat Crafting[/b] — Recipe visibility filters applied through NC_FilterBar; runtime-detected, no hard dependency
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Content Summary[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]276 recipes[/b] across blackpowder, biodiesel, soap, bone char, salt extraction, recycling, agriculture, concrete mixer, botanical, utility, and advanced lab pathways
[*] [b]101 items[/b] including chemical reagents, intermediates, container variants, gardening sprays, construction materials, salt products, botanical textiles, horticulture products, and smoking items
[*] [b]59 tradeable items[/b] registered with Dynamic Trading across 9 vendor archetypes
[*] [b]6 recipe books[/b] (5 category primers + 1 master compendium) teaching recipes by pathway
[*] [b]5 skill books[/b] covering Applied Chemistry levels 1-10
[*] [b]2 occupations[/b] (Chemist, Pharmacist) and [b]2 traits[/b] (Chemistry Enthusiast, Chemical Aversion)
[*] [b]9 fluids[/b] with Build 42 FluidContainer integration and poison profiles
[*] [b]19 sandbox options[/b] for gameplay customization, vessel replacement, concrete mixer, botanical pathway, and maintenance
[*] [b]216 OnCreate callbacks[/b] for purity tracking, vessel replacement, and item processing
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Sandbox Options[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Yield Multiplier[/b] (0.25-4.0) — Scale recipe output quantities
[*] [b]Advanced Lab Recipes[/b] — Gate microscope and spectrometer recipes
[*] [b]Require Heat Sources[/b] — Gate fuel requirements on heated recipes
[*] [b]Impurity System[/b] — Enable purity tracking through recipe chains
[*] [b]Impurity Severity[/b] (Mild/Standard/Harsh) — Control purity degradation intensity
[*] [b]Skill Purity Influence[/b] (None/Low/Standard/High) — Control how Applied Chemistry skill affects purity
[*] [b]Health Hazards[/b] — Enable Protected/Unprotected recipe variants
[*] [b]Botanical Pathway[/b] — Enable/disable hemp processing recipes and horticulture items
[*] [b]Vessel Replacement[/b] — Replace empty PCP containers with vanilla vessels on open
[*] [b]Concrete Mixer[/b] — Enable/disable mixer, output yield multiplier, generator fuel drain rate
[*] [b]Maintenance/Reset[/b] — Six one-shot reset/migration options for upgrades and mod removal
[*] [b]Migrate Horticulture[/b] — One-shot conversion of [B42] Horticulture items to PCP equivalents
[/list]

